An HTTP/1.0 endpoint that classifies a request and writes a complete
audit trail line per request: receipt timestamp, request method and path,
response status, and response body. The line is JSONL — one JSON object
per request, the format SIEM pipelines (Splunk, Loki, Elastic) and an
Article 12 audit processor consume directly.

The handler returns 200 with body "ok" for GET /, 200 with body "ping"
for GET /ping, and 404 with body "not found" otherwise. The handler
itself reads only req.method and req.path; it never observes the
timestamp, so the response is fully reproducible from the (method, path)
pair. The clock read happens once per accept loop and is exposed only to
the log scope, which is what makes verdict and audit independent.
